@startuml
!define RECTANGLE class

title MicroServicesPOC - Deployment and Control Flow Sequence Diagram

actor "API Client" as Client
participant "Order Service\nController" as OrderCtrl
participant "Order Service\nRepository" as OrderRepo
database "MongoDB\n(Order DB)" as OrderDB
participant "MassTransit\n(Order Service)" as OrderMT
queue "RabbitMQ\nMessage Broker" as RabbitMQ
participant "Customer Service\nConsumer" as CustomerConsumer
participant "Customer Service\nRepository" as CustomerRepo
database "MongoDB\n(Customer DB)" as CustomerDB
participant "Catalog Service\nConsumer" as CatalogConsumer
participant "Catalog Service\nRepository" as CatalogRepo
database "MongoDB\n(Catalog DB)" as CatalogDB

== Service Initialization & Deployment ==

note over OrderCtrl, OrderDB
  Docker Compose deploys Order Service
  with MongoDB connection and RabbitMQ config
end note

note over CustomerConsumer, CustomerDB
  Docker Compose deploys Customer Service
  with MongoDB connection and RabbitMQ config
end note

note over CatalogConsumer, CatalogDB
  Docker Compose deploys Catalog Service
  with MongoDB connection and RabbitMQ config
end note

OrderMT -> RabbitMQ: Subscribe to events
CustomerConsumer -> RabbitMQ: Subscribe to OrderCreated,\nOrderUpdated, OrderRemoved
CatalogConsumer -> RabbitMQ: Subscribe to relevant events

== Order Creation Flow ==

Client -> OrderCtrl: POST /orders (Create Order)
activate OrderCtrl

OrderCtrl -> OrderRepo: Save order entity
activate OrderRepo
OrderRepo -> OrderDB: Insert order document
activate OrderDB
OrderDB --> OrderRepo: Confirmation
deactivate OrderDB
OrderRepo --> OrderCtrl: Order saved
deactivate OrderRepo

OrderCtrl -> OrderMT: Publish OrderCreated event
activate OrderMT
OrderMT -> RabbitMQ: Send OrderCreated event
activate RabbitMQ
OrderMT --> OrderCtrl: Event published
deactivate OrderMT

OrderCtrl --> Client: 201 Created (Order response)
deactivate OrderCtrl

RabbitMQ -> CustomerConsumer: Deliver OrderCreated event
activate CustomerConsumer
deactivate RabbitMQ

CustomerConsumer -> CustomerRepo: Update customer order history
activate CustomerRepo
CustomerRepo -> CustomerDB: Update customer document\n(add order to history)
activate CustomerDB
CustomerDB --> CustomerRepo: Update confirmed
deactivate CustomerDB
CustomerRepo --> CustomerConsumer: Customer updated
deactivate CustomerRepo
CustomerConsumer --> RabbitMQ: Acknowledge event
deactivate CustomerConsumer

== Order Update Flow ==

Client -> OrderCtrl: PUT /orders/{id} (Update Order)
activate OrderCtrl

OrderCtrl -> OrderRepo: Update order entity
activate OrderRepo
OrderRepo -> OrderDB: Update order document
activate OrderDB
OrderDB --> OrderRepo: Confirmation
deactivate OrderDB
OrderRepo --> OrderCtrl: Order updated
deactivate OrderRepo

OrderCtrl -> OrderMT: Publish OrderUpdated event
activate OrderMT
OrderMT -> RabbitMQ: Send OrderUpdated event
activate RabbitMQ
OrderMT --> OrderCtrl: Event published
deactivate OrderMT

OrderCtrl --> Client: 200 OK (Updated order)
deactivate OrderCtrl

RabbitMQ -> CustomerConsumer: Deliver OrderUpdated event
activate CustomerConsumer
deactivate RabbitMQ

CustomerConsumer -> CustomerRepo: Update customer order history
activate CustomerRepo
CustomerRepo -> CustomerDB: Update customer document\n(modify order in history)
activate CustomerDB
CustomerDB --> CustomerRepo: Update confirmed
deactivate CustomerDB
CustomerRepo --> CustomerConsumer: Customer updated
deactivate CustomerRepo
CustomerConsumer --> RabbitMQ: Acknowledge event
deactivate CustomerConsumer

== Catalog Item Creation Flow ==

Client -> CatalogConsumer: POST /catalog (Create Item)
note right: Simplified - actually goes\nthrough Catalog Controller
activate CatalogConsumer

CatalogConsumer -> CatalogRepo: Save catalog item
activate CatalogRepo
CatalogRepo -> CatalogDB: Insert catalog document
activate CatalogDB
CatalogDB --> CatalogRepo: Confirmation
deactivate CatalogDB
CatalogRepo --> CatalogConsumer: Item saved
deactivate CatalogRepo

CatalogConsumer -> RabbitMQ: Publish CatalogItemCreated event
activate RabbitMQ
RabbitMQ --> CatalogConsumer: Event published
deactivate RabbitMQ

CatalogConsumer --> Client: 201 Created
deactivate CatalogConsumer

RabbitMQ -> OrderMT: Deliver CatalogItemCreated event
activate OrderMT
OrderMT -> OrderRepo: Update local catalog registry\n(Anti-corruption layer)
activate OrderRepo
OrderRepo -> OrderDB: Update catalog cache
activate OrderDB
OrderDB --> OrderRepo: Update confirmed
deactivate OrderDB
OrderRepo --> OrderMT: Registry updated
deactivate OrderRepo
OrderMT --> RabbitMQ: Acknowledge event
deactivate OrderMT

== Health Check Monitoring ==

Client -> OrderCtrl: GET /health
activate OrderCtrl
OrderCtrl -> OrderDB: Check MongoDB health
activate OrderDB
OrderDB --> OrderCtrl: Healthy
deactivate OrderDB
OrderCtrl -> RabbitMQ: Check RabbitMQ health
activate RabbitMQ
RabbitMQ --> OrderCtrl: Healthy
deactivate RabbitMQ
OrderCtrl --> Client: 200 OK (Health status)
deactivate OrderCtrl

note over Client, CatalogDB
  All services expose health check endpoints
  monitored by AspNetCore.Diagnostics.HealthChecks dashboard
end note

@enduml
